英國畫家{{le|格雷厄姆·薩瑟蘭|Graham Sutherland}}於1954年獲委託，為時任英國首相的[[溫斯頓·丘吉爾|溫斯頓·丘吉爾]]繪製畫像，作為丘吉爾80歲壽辰的賀禮<ref name="LostArt">{{cite web|title=An Introduction to Graham Sutherland's Portrait of Sir Winston Churchill|url=http://galleryoflostart.com/blog/artist/graham-sutherland/portrait-of-sir-winston-churchill/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120720013509/http://galleryoflostart.com/blog/artist/graham-sutherland/portrait-of-sir-winston-churchill/|archive-date=20 July 2012|work=galleryoflostart.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=1954: Winston Churchill turns 80|work=On This Day, 30 November 1954|publisher=BBC|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/november/30/newsid_3280000/3280401.stm|accessdate=2021-01-11|archive-date=2020-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101183254/http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/november/30/newsid_3280000/3280401.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。丘吉爾對此畫像感到極度厭惡，因此在[[西敏宮#西敏廳|西敏廳]]的公開贈送儀式後，並未有將之展示出來，而是藏於其[[查特韋爾莊園|查特韋爾莊園]]中<ref name="#1">{{cite book |title = The People's Almanac Book of Lists |editor1-first = David |editor1-last = Wallechinsky |editor2-first = Irving |editor2-last = Wallace |editor3-first = Amy |editor3-last = Wallace |year = 1984 |page = 190 |chapter = 10 people who hated portraits of themselves |first = Roy W. |last = Sorrels |isbn = 0-552-12371-4 }}</ref>。在其妻子[[克萊門汀·丘吉爾|克萊門汀·丘吉爾]]於1977年死後，人们发现她在獲得此畫像數月後，已經將之焚毀，以宣洩她丈夫的怒火<ref name="tele">{{cite news |url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/winston-churchill/11730850/Secret-of-Winston-Churchills-unpopular-Sutherland-portrait-revealed.html |title = Secret of Winston Churchill's unpopular Sutherland portrait revealed |date = 10 July 2015 |work = The Telegraph |location = London |accessdate = 2021-01-11 |archive-date = 2017-07-31 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170731185510/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/winston-churchill/11730850/Secret-of-Winston-Churchills-unpopular-Sutherland-portrait-revealed.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。

== 背景 ==
畫像繪製之時，丘吉爾已經是年紀老邁第二任期將盡的首相。薩瑟蘭則是一個已有一定聲譽，以沒有修飾手法見稱的[[現代主義|現代主義]]畫家<ref name="LostArt"/>。他們對畫像抱有不同的期望。丘吉爾希望被描繪成披着長袍的[[嘉德勋章|受勳騎士]]，但委託人要求畫中人穿著普通國會的服飾。

== 準備工作 ==
1954年8月，丘吉爾與薩瑟蘭在查特韋爾莊園會面了三數次，薩瑟蘭以炭筆起了幾幅初稿，專注於丘吉爾的手和臉部。完成初稿後，薩瑟蘭返回工作室，並在大號方形帆布上開始創作此畫像。畫布的形狀象徵着丘吉爾的堅毅與耐力，體現了丘吉爾的名言「我是磐石」。畫中丘吉爾握緊椅子扶手的坐姿參照了[[美國|美國]][[林肯纪念堂|林肯纪念堂]]中林肯雕像的坐姿。畫像描繪的丘吉爾皺着眉頭，略微前傾，周圍被冷漠的灰色、棕色和黑色調所包圍。製作期間，薩瑟蘭不願與丘吉爾談論進度，或展示其作品。丘吉爾太太認為畫得非常神似，但有點兒太過真實。其兒子{{le|倫道夫·丘吉爾|Randolph Churchill|倫道夫}}則覺得畫像顯得其父親一臉不快。

== 反響 ==
丘吉爾太太在1954年11月20日看過完成的畫像之後拍了一張照片並帶了給她的丈夫。這是丘吉爾首次看到畫像並心感不安。他及後向[[查爾斯·威爾遜，第一代莫蘭男爵|莫蘭男爵]]形容此畫像為骯髒及立壞心腸<ref name="Pearson">{{cite book |last1=Pearson |first1=John |title=The private lives of Winston Churchill |date=2012 |publisher=Bloomsbury Reader |location=London |isbn=9781448208074 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LOyIFMhshAQC&pg=PT338 |access-date=27 June 2018}}</ref>，投訴畫像將他畫成從排水溝中救起出來的醉漢的模樣<ref name="Distillations">{{cite journal|last1=Meyer|first1=Michal|title=Sketch of a Scientist|url=https://www.sciencehistory.org/distillations/magazine/sketch-of-a-scientist|journal=Distillations|publisher=[[Science_History_Institute|Science History Institute]]|date=2018|volume=4|issue=1|pages=10–11|access-date=27 June 2018|archive-date=2021-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210414230654/https://www.sciencehistory.org/distillations/magazine/sketch-of-a-scientist|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Lacey">{{cite book |last1=Lacey |first1=Robert |title=The Crown: The Official Companion, Volume 1 Elizabeth II, Winston Churchill, and the Making of a Young Queen (1947-1955) |date=17 October 2017 |publisher=Crown Archetype |isbn=9781524762285|volume=1 }}</ref>。由於距離贈送儀式只差10日，丘吉爾至函薩瑟蘭，形容畫像雖然是大師級製作但並不適宜<ref name="Distillations"/>，儀式將如期舉行但畫像則不會被發佈。薩瑟蘭回覆重新畫像誠實和現實地反映了他對丘吉爾的印象。{{le|查爾斯·道蒂|Charles Doughty (politician)}}議員則遊說丘吉爾，着他不可阻礙發佈，免得冒犯出資贊助是次委託的國會議員<ref name="Black">{{cite book |last1=Black |first1=Jonathan |title=Winston Churchill in British Art, 1900 to the Present Day: The Titan With |pages=154–170 |date=23 March 2017 |publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing |isbn=9781472592415 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GJBHDgAAQBAJ&pg=PA154 |access-date=27 June 2018 |archive-date=2020-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201219131340/https://books.google.com/books?id=GJBHDgAAQBAJ&pg=PA154 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在贈送儀式的謝詞中，丘吉爾稱此畫像為現代藝術的傑出典範（該段發言被認為是反諷）。各界對此畫像的反應不一，有評論家稱讚畫像與丘吉爾甚為相似，亦有人譴責它為恥辱<ref name="#1"/>。

